## ðŸ§© 1. TERMINAL SETUP
```bash
//? --- Basic project setup ---
python -m venv venv                # Create virtual environment
venv\Scripts\activate              # Activate on Windows
# OR
source venv/bin/activate           # Activate on macOS/Linux

//? --- Install dependencies ---
pip install Flask
pip install Flask-SQLAlchemy
pip install pytz
pip install gunicorn               # optional, for production
pip install python-dotenv          # manage environment variables

//? --- Freeze requirements ---
pip freeze > requirements.txt      # save dependencies

//? --- Initialize database ---
flask init-db                      # creates lost_items.db and log.db

//? --- Run the application ---
flask run                          # launch Flask server
# OR
python app.py                      # alternate run command
````

---

## ðŸ§  2. GIT COMMANDS

```bash
//? --- Standard workflow ---
git add .                          # stage all changes
git commit -m "your message"       # commit changes
git push -u origin main            # push to GitHub

//! --- Undo / Reset (use carefully) ---
git reset                          # unstage files (before commit)
git reset --hard                   # discard all uncommitted changes
```

---

## ðŸ§° 3. EXTRA UTILITIES

```bash
//? --- Clear cache ---
python -m pip cache info
python -m pip cache purge

//? --- Clear terminal cache in VS Code ---
# Press: Alt + F7

//? --- Generate requirements anytime ---
python -m pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

